flds.val: while reading a stored entry using data descriptor. Either the archive is broken or it can not be read using ZipArchiveInputStream and you must use ZipFile. A common cause for this is a ZIP archive containing a ZIP archive. See https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-compress/zip.html#ZipArchiveInputStream_vs_ZipFile
Archive's size exceeds the limit of 4GByte.
Number of the disk with the start of Central Directory exceeds the limit of 65535.
The size of the entire central directory exceeds the limit of 4GByte.
Number of the disk of End Of Central Directory exceeds the limit of 65535.
Number of entries on this disk exceeds the limit of 65535.
Zip64 extended information must contain both size values in the local file header.
